label.value: increased total RNA level during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the total amount of RNA measured in a cell is higher than normal.

label.value: abnormal cell cycle arrest at mitotic G2/M phase transition following single cell division during nitrogen starvation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which progression through the mitotic cell cycle is arrested at the mitotic G2/M phase transition, instead of the normal G1 phase, and after the cell undergoes one cell division instead of the normal two, when the cell is subject to nitrogen starvation.

definition.value: This term can be used for any circumstances in which cells are starved for nitrogen. Note that cells may enter G0 (quiescence) when subjected to prolonged nitrogen starvation; this term is not restricted to G0. This term differs from 'abnormal cell cycle arrest at mitotic G2/M phase transition during nitrogen starvation' (FYPO:0001001) because it additionally specifies a single cell division, and from 'single cell division prior to G0 entry' (FYPO:0003877) because it does not apply only to G0, and does specify arrest in G2.

label.value: decreased duration of meiotic cell cycle phase

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the duration of one or more meiotic cell cycle phases is shorter than normal.

label.value: decreased duration of meiotic S phase

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the duration of progression through S phase of the meiotic cell cycle (preceding meiosis I) is shorter than normal.

label.value: increased protein localization to medial cortex during mitotic telophase

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to the medial cortex is increased during mitotic telophase.

definition.value: Encompasses both presence of proteins not normally found at the medial cortex and decreased levels or absence of proteins normally found there, and describes defects in a localization process. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal growth on EGTA

value.value: A phenotype in which vegetative cell population growth is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) in a medium containing EGTA.

label.value: abnormal histone H3-K37 methylation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which methylation of lysine at position 37 of histone H3 is abnormal.

label.value: increased histone H3-K37 methylation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which methylation of lysine at position 37 of histone H3 is increased.

label.value: decreased histone H3-K37 methylation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which methylation of lysine at position 37 of histone H3 is decreased.

label.value: abolished histone H3-K37 methylation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which methylation of lysine at position 37 of histone H3 does not occur.

label.value: decreased mitotic DNA replication at telomere

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the occurrence of DNA replication is decreased in telomeric regions.

label.value: decreased mitotic DNA replication at rDNA

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the occurrence of DNA replication is decreased in ribosomal DNA repeats.

label.value: mislocalized RNA during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which an RNA is observed in a particular location where it is not normally found.

label.value: RNA mislocalized to cytoplasm during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which an RNA that is not normally found in the cytoplasm is observed there.

label.value: loss of viability following cellular response to bleomycin

value.value: A cell population phenotype in which a smaller than normal proportion of cells in the population remains viable after exposure to bleomycin.

definition.value: Use this term to annotate experiments in which a culture is grown in the presence of hydroxyurea, and then the number of cells viable enough to form a colony upon hydroxyurea removal is measured and compared to wild type.

label.value: normal mitotic DNA damage checkpoint during cellular response to streptonigrin

value.value: A cell cycle checkpoint phenotype in which any mitotic DNA damage checkpoint is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) when the cell is exposed to streptonigrin. A DNA damage checkpoint normally regulates progression through the cell cycle in response to DNA damage.

label.value: increased rate of protein exchange in actomyosin contractile ring

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the rate, or speed, of protein exchange in the actomyosin contractile ring is increased. Normally, proteins including actin and myosin are turned over between the contractile ring and elsewhere in the cytoplasm; exchange is faster during than before ring constriction.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal protein localization to cell cortex

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to the cell cortex is abnormal.

definition.value: Encompasses both presence of proteins not normally found at the cell cortex and decreased levels or absence of proteins normally found there, and describes defects in a localization process. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein localization to cell cortex during meiotic prophase I

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to the cell cortex is decreased during prophase of the first meiotic nuclear division.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished histone H3-K36 methylation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which methylation of lysine at position 36 of histone H3 does not occur.

label.value: abnormal histone methylation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which histone methylation is abnormal. All histone methylation may be affected, or methylation of specific sites on specific histones may be altered.

label.value: increased protein phosphorylation during cellular response to ionizing radiation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the phosphorylation of one or more specific proteins, or of specific protein sites, occurs to a greater extent than normal during a cellular response to ionizing radiation.

definition.value: Also consider annotating to 'increased protein phosphorylation during cellular response to DNA damage' (FYPO:0002095). When using this term, it is recommended to note the specific protein(s) affected.

label.value: increased histone H2A phosphorylation during cellular response to ionizing radiation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which histone H2A phosphorylation occurs to a greater extent than normal during a cellular response to ionizing radiation. All histone H2A phosphorylation may be affected, or phosphorylation of specific sites on histone H2A may be increased.

label.value: protein mislocalized to cell cortex of cell tip

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a protein that is not normally found in the cell cortex at one or both cell tips is observed there.

definition.value: Note that this term can be used to annotate any case where a protein is found at the non-growing cell tip in a mutant, but not in wild type. In some cases, there may be enough additional information to annotate to 'abnormal protein localization' (FYPO:0000443) or one of its descendants. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased protein localization to cell cortex of old growing cell tip

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the cell cortex at an old growing cell tip is increased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal protein localization to cell cortex of cell tip during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the cell cortex of one or both cell tips is abnormal.

definition.value: Encompasses both presence of proteins not normally found at the cell cortex and decreased levels or absence of proteins normally found there, and describes defects in a localization process. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein localization to cell cortex of cell tip

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to the cell cortex of the cell tip is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: inviable after spore germination, multiple cell divisions, cell lysis during cytokinesis

value.value: A phenotype in which a spore germinates to produce an inviable cell that undergoes two or more rounds of cell division, but then lyses during cytokinesis and dies.

label.value: inviable after spore germination, multiple cell divisions, with abnormal septation

value.value: A phenotype in which a spore germinates to produce a cell of normal morphology (i.e. size, shape, and structure) that undergoes two or more rounds of cell division in which septum assembly is abnormal, and then dies.

label.value: normal cleavage furrow ingression

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cleavage furrow ingression is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: increased protein localization to center of cell division site

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the center (as observed end-on) of the site of cell division is increased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased cellular phytoceramide level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of a phytoceramide measured in a cell is lower than normal.

label.value: imperforate nuclear envelope

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the nuclear envelope is imperforate (i.e. has no openings in the membranes, like wild type).

definition.value: Note that an abnormal nuclear envelope organization process may, but does not necessarily, result in abnormal nuclear envelope morphology.

label.value: decreased exocytosis at cell division site

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which exocytosis occurs to a lower extent than normal at the cell division site.

label.value: thick mitotic spindle during mitotic metaphase

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the mitotic spindle is thicker than normal during mitotic metaphase.

definition.value: In images of thin spindles, polar microtubules may appear not to reach continuously from pole to pole.

label.value: decreased protein level at mitotic spindle

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of a protein measured at or associated with the mitotic spindle is lower than normal.

definition.value: Use this term for cases where the relative abundance of one or more specific proteins in the proteasome is decreased, altering the proteasome stoichiometry. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased protein level at mitotic spindle

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of a protein measured at or associated with the mitotic spindle is greater than normal.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein sumoylation during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the sumoylation of one or more specific proteins, or of specific protein sites, is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein localization to plasma membrane during iron starvation

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the plasma membrane is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) when the cell is subject to iron ion starvation.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased cellular iron level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of iron ion measured in a cell is lower than normal.

label.value: decreased heme export from vacuole

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the occurrence of heme export from the vacuole to the cytoplasm is decreased.

label.value: abnormal inositol hexakisphosphate kinase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of inositol hexakisphosphate kinase activity is abnormal.

label.value: abolished inositol hexakisphosphate kinase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which inositol hexakisphosphate kinase activity is absent.

label.value: decreased inositol hexakisphosphate kinase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of inositol hexakisphosphate kinase activity is decreased.

label.value: increased inositol hexakisphosphate kinase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of inositol hexakisphosphate kinase activity is increased.

label.value: decreased protein localization to cell tip during meiosis

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to the cell tip is decreased during one or both meiotic nuclear divisions.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased mitochondrion localization to cell tip during meiosis

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of mitochondria to the cell tip is decreased during one or both meiotic nuclear divisions.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased rate of actomyosin contractile ring contraction

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the rate, or speed, of actomyosin contractile ring contraction is increased. Contractile ring contraction is the part of cytokinesis in which the actomyosin contractile ring constricts.

label.value: normal cell wall thickness during vegetative growth

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the thickness of the cell wall is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: asymmetric cell separation after cytokinesis

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cell separation after cytokinesis is abnormally asymmetric, i.e. cells separate asymmetrically by usually detaching one side of the new ends before the other. Normally, separate symmetrically by detaching both sides of the new ends from each other simultaneously.

definition.value: This phenotype usually results from a defect late in septum degradation.
